HEADWORD: Diathermometer
<hw>Di`a*ther*mom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
warm + <ets>-meter</ets>. See <er>Diathermal</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for examining the thermal
resistance or heat-conducting power of liquids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

